---
import PolicyPageShell from '../components/public/PolicyPageShell.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms | CryptoPayMap"
  description="Public-site and contribution terms for using CryptoPayMap information, submitting material, and understanding review and publication boundaries."
>
  <PolicyPageShell
    eyebrow="Terms"
    title="Terms of Use"
    description="These terms describe the operating boundary of the public site and the conditions that apply when contribution intake is enabled."
  >
    <div class="grid gap-9">
      <section class="rounded-card border border-border bg-surface p-5 shadow-sm sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Use of the public site</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          CryptoPayMap provides reviewed information about cryptocurrency payment acceptance. You may use the public site and machine-readable public files for lawful purposes subject to the applicable data, text, source, and media license boundaries described on the Sources and Licenses page.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          You must not use the service to interfere with its operation, attempt unauthorized access, bypass access controls, submit malicious content, impersonate another person or business, or misuse private status links and restricted material.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Public records and review</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 grid list-disc gap-2 pl-5 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          <li>A source, submission, import, or directory listing does not automatically become a public record.</li>
          <li>Candidate material remains private until an explicit review and publication decision.</li>
          <li>CryptoPayMap may correct, mark stale, mark ended, temporarily hide, or remove public material when evidence, rights, privacy, legal, or safety review requires it.</li>
          <li>Publication decisions are based on the verification and source policies, not payment, sponsorship, or partnership status.</li>
          <li>A business relationship does not create a right to remove accurate public history, while valid factual, privacy, rights, and legal correction requests remain reviewable.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-card border border-border bg-brand-50 p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Contribution terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          When contribution intake is enabled, submitting information does not guarantee publication, confirmation, a particular review result, or a specific completion time. A submission may be approved, partially approved, accepted as a private candidate, held for more information, closed with no change, or not approved.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 grid list-disc gap-2 pl-5 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          <li>Submit information you reasonably believe is accurate and applicable to the identified place or service.</li>
          <li>Do not submit private keys, seed phrases, unrelated credentials, unnecessary personal data, or material you are not authorized to provide.</li>
          <li>Evidence-only permission allows private receipt, storage, validation, and review; it does not automatically authorize public gallery display.</li>
          <li>For public-gallery media, the contributor confirms ownership or authority and grants CryptoPayMap a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free permission to host, display, resize, crop, re-encode, create responsive derivatives, use the media on the applicable listing and project promotion, and remove it when required.</li>
          <li>The contributor retains ownership of submitted public-gallery media, and general public data or text licenses do not automatically apply to that media.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Availability and changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          Features, routes, data files, and contribution workflows may change as the product develops. Public product releases are recorded in the Changelog, while changes to acceptance records are shown in Updates. Service availability may be interrupted for maintenance, incidents, provider outages, or security response.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-card border border-border bg-surface p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">License boundaries</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          Public data, OpenStreetMap-derived fields, project-authored explanatory text, software code, trademarks, and media do not share one automatic license. Use the source, attribution, and license information applicable to the specific component you reuse.
        </p>
        <a class="mt-3 inline-flex min-h-11 items-center font-semibold text-brand-700" href="/sources-and-licenses">
          Review Sources and Licenses
        </a>
      </section>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 border-t border-border pt-6">
        <a class="motion-feedback inline-flex min-h-11 items-center rounded-control bg-brand-600 px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-white no-underline hover:bg-brand-700" href="/disclaimer">
          Read the disclaimer
        </a>
        <a class="motion-feedback inline-flex min-h-11 items-center rounded-control border border-border px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-ink no-underline hover:bg-brand-50" href="/privacy">
          Read Privacy
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </PolicyPageShell>
</BaseLayout>
